--- !u!114 &1599553132
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 1599553130}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: f4688fdb7df04437aeb418b961361dc5, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  m_Material: {fileID: 0}
  m_Color: {r: 1, g: 1, b: 1, a: 1}
  m_RaycastTarget: 1
  m_RaycastPadding: {x: 0, y: 0, z: 0, w: 0}
  m_Maskable: 1
  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: "In <b>Scoundrel</b>, your goal is to defeat each 4-card room in the dungeon
    until you \nreach the end of the deck. \nWhenever you enter a room you are presented
    with four cards:\n\r\n- <color=#930000><b>DIAMONDS</b></color> are <u>weapons</u>
    - their power is equal to their value. \r\n\t- If you equip a weapon it replaces
    your current one\n\r\n- <color=#930000><b>HEARTS</b></color> are <u>potions</u>
    - they heal you equal to your value\r\n\t- Only your FIRST potion per room will
    count; any others rest will be discarded if used.\n\r\n- <color=#405A8C><b>CLUBS</b></color>
    and <color=#405A8C><b>SPADES</b></color> are <u>monsters</u> - you may attack
    them with your weapon (if you have one) or your fists:\r\n\t- <u>Weapon:</u>
    You take damage equal to the difference of the monster's value vs your weapon's
    and defeat it\r\n\t\t  Your weapon can only attack a monster with a value LOWER
    than the previously slain monster\r\n\t- <u>Fists:</u> You take damage equal
    to the monster's value and defeat it\r\n\r\nYou may take cards in any order.\r\n\r\nYou
    may <u><b>run</b></u> from a room if it seems too dangerous. It gets placed back
    on the bottom of the deck.\r\nHowever you may <u>never</u> run from a room twice
    in a row.\r\n\r\nWhen a room is down to its last card, or no cards, you may move
    into the next room.\r\nIf the room still has a card in it when you go into the
    next, the next room contains that card.\r\n\r\nIf your health reaches 0, you
    <u><b>die</b></u>.\r\n\r\nIf you defeat every monster in the deck, you <u><b>win</b></u>!\r\n\n<color=#767676>Scoundrel
    was originally designed by Zach Gage and Kurt Bieg.</color>"
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 75264fa9e13da2b41919fefa895e40a6, type: 2}
